"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45429","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-02","<p /> <p /> <p>Of the 28 workers made redundant as a result of the closure of Remploy in South Gyle, Edinburgh we are able to provide information on the 24 disabled former employees who have engaged with a Personal Case Worker.</p><p> </p><p>As at 21 March 2014 Jobcentre Plus records show that 7 people are in paid employment over 16 hours and 17 have accessed Work Choice support. We have no records of people working a) less than 16 hours, b) less than 30 hours per week paid employment or c) in voluntary and unpaid work</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45429/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-02T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45429/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45429/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer to the hon. Member for Edinburgh West of 10 February 2014, Official Report, column 515W, on Remploy: Edinburgh, how many former Remploy employees from the Edinburgh site are working (a) less than 16 hours per week in paid employment, (b) less than 30 hours per week in paid employment and (c) in voluntary and unpaid positions.","false","Biography information for Teresa Pearce","Erith and Thamesmead","Teresa Pearce","193821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45430","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-03-31","<p /> <p /> <p>The information requested is not available. Designation as supported exempt accomodation is relevant only to claims by individuals for Housing Benefit and is not intrinsic to the definition or purpose of a refuge or other supported housing.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45430/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45430/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45430/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many refuges are not classed as supported exempt accommodation for the purposes of housing benefit.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","193783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45431","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-03-31","<p /> <p /> <p>Since Universal Jobmatch was launched in November 2012, we have introduced additional checks on all new vacancies placed by new employer accounts.</p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45431/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45431/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45431/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 25 March 2014, Official Report, column 233W, on vacancies: internet, what additional checks and safeguards for jobseekers have been introduced in each year since the launch of Universal Jobmatch.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","193824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45432","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-02","<p /> <p /> <p>The Health and Safety Executive has not taken any action to mandate or recommend the use of automated traffic management equipment to lift and lay cones.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The highway maintenance industry has trialled cone laying machines and the decision to use such machines rests with them on a commercial operational basis</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45432/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-02T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45432/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45432/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps the Health and Safety Executive has taken to recommend or mandate the use of automated traffic management technology to lift and lay cones on the motorway network in the last 10 years for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","193977"
