"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44668","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p>Each local authority that administers a pension fund is already subject to statutory guidance that states that it should recognise the Financial Reporting Council's Stewardship Code and ensure that the Code is adopted by their fund managers, investment consultants and advisers. The guidance also states that the authority should include a statement of its policy on responsible ownership in its statement of the principles governing its investment decisions and report periodically to scheme members on the implementation of the policy. Sixteen of the eighty nine local government pension funds in England and Wales are themselves signatories to the Stewardship Code as asset owners.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44668/answer",,,,,"193481","2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44668/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44668/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to encourage local authority pension funds to become signatories to the Stewardship Code.","false","Biography information for Paul Uppal","Wolverhampton South West","Paul Uppal","193480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44669","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p>Each local authority that administers a pension fund is already subject to statutory guidance that states that it should recognise the Financial Reporting Council's Stewardship Code and ensure that the Code is adopted by their fund managers, investment consultants and advisers. The guidance also states that the authority should include a statement of its policy on responsible ownership in its statement of the principles governing its investment decisions and report periodically to scheme members on the implementation of the policy. Sixteen of the eighty nine local government pension funds in England and Wales are themselves signatories to the Stewardship Code as asset owners.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44669/answer",,,,,"193480","2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44669/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44669/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to encourage local authority pension funds to become active owners or stewards of their assets as defined in the Financial Reporting Council's Stewardship Code.","false","Biography information for Paul Uppal","Wolverhampton South West","Paul Uppal","193481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44670","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-03","<p>These issues are matters for individual local authorities that administer pension funds to consider when deciding upon their investment strategies. Each administering authority is required to publish a statement of principles, which should address such issues. Statutory guidance states that the authority must report periodically to scheme members on the implementation of their policies.</p><p>Notwithstanding, local authorities need to focus on delivering a good rate of return for their fund and value for taxpayers, given local government pensions cost taxpayers (via employer contributions) almost £6 billion a year.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44670/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44670/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44670/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent assessment he has made of the need for local authority pension schemes to integrate environmental, social and governance issues into their investment decision-making.","false","Biography information for Paul Uppal","Wolverhampton South West","Paul Uppal","193479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44672","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p><em>[Holding Reply: Thursday 27 March 2014]</em></p><p>In July 2009, 100 local authorities submitted proposals to the Selector, the Local Government Association. In December 2009, the Selector presented a short-list of 199 proposals, containing over 300 separate requests to the Government. Details of these proposals, the 39 actions this Government said it would take in response and an update on these actions that was published in July last year can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/sustainable-communities-act-2007-decisions-on-local-councils-proposals-to-improve-local-areas" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/sustainable-communities-act-2007-decisions-on-local-councils-proposals-to-improve-local-areas</a></p><p>Five local authorities submitted proposals in 2011. We carefully considered all the proposals and took forward two firm proposals. One local authority has submitted a proposal this year. It is under consideration.</p><p>The Government extended the power to submit proposals under the Act to town and parish councils in October last year. Since then five town and parish councils have submitted proposals, which are under consideration.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Bristol West","Stephen Williams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44672/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44672/answer","Biography information for Stephen Williams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44672/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many proposals have been made by local authorities under the Sustainable Communities Act 2007 in each year since that Act has been in force; and how many such proposals his Department has adopted.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","193399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44675","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>The Government does not impose a particular level of affordable housing for housing schemes. The percentage of affordable units will be a matter for local decision making taking account of the local authorities' local plans and site viability. Unrealistic Section 106 agreements result in no development, no regeneration and no community benefits.</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44675/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44675/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44675/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of the development announced in Budget 2014 at Ebbsfleet will consist of affordable homes.","false","Biography information for Dr Roberta Blackman-Woods","City of Durham","Roberta Blackman-Woods","193427"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44678","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by the Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General, the right hon. Member for Horsham on 26 March 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, column 300W.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44678/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44678/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44678/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what his Department's policy is on allowing officials to appear before all-party parliamentary groups.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","193383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44680","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p><em>[Holding Reply: Monday 31 March 2014]</em></p><p>We expect the new Ebbsfleet Urban Development Corporation, once established, to develop the vision for Ebbsfleet Garden City in co-operation with local partners.</p><p>We would expect the Corporation, working with local partners and other experts, to consider how accepted Garden Cities principles, such as high quality, imaginative design, the provision of generous green space, mixed tenure homes and a strong local jobs offer, could be delivered in a way appropriate to local needs and circumstances.</p><p>The Government wants Ebbsfleet to set high standards in terms of design quality. The Built for Life principles are industry developed standards for good design. We would look to those coming forward with development proposals at Ebbsfleet to adopt them, and encourage them to be ambitious by aiming for a ‘green' rating.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44680/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44680/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44680/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to establish garden city principles in Ebbsfleet.","false","Biography information for Dr Roberta Blackman-Woods","City of Durham","Roberta Blackman-Woods","193458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44692","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-04-07","<p>The 2010 National Security Strategy and the Strategic Defence and Security Review (SDSR) set the top level political direction and guidance for UK Defence. Defence Strategic Direction (DSD) translates this top level direction into broad priorities for Defence but it does not set specific goals, or relate to specific missions, activities or threats, and it would not be appropriate or practical to update DSD in the face of each individual crisis or threat.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44692/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44692/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44692/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will update the Defence Strategic Guidance to reflect the Russian annexation of the Crimea.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","193347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44694","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-03-31","<p> </p><p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer given by the Minister for the Cabinet Office on 26 Mar 2014, Column 300W.</p><p> </p>","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44694/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44694/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44694/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what his Office's policy is on allowing officials to appear before all-party parliamentary groups.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","193385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44696","Department for Education","false","2014-03-31","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given to the hon. Member for Cardiff West on 24 March, Official Report column 84W.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44696/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44696/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44696/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Statement of 13 March 2014 by the Minister for Schools, Official Report, columns 927-29, how much of the £350 million announced for the fair funding proposals will be allocated from the Exchequer in addition to that already indicated in his Department's budget.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","193407"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44697","Department for Education","false","2014-03-31","<p>I refer the Rt. hon member to the response of 26 March 2014, Hansard column 300W, provided by the Cabinet Office.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44697/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44697/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44697/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what his Department's policy is on allowing officials to appear before all-party parliamentary groups.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","193386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44698","Department for Education","false","2014-03-31","<p>The Department for Education does not collect information on the number of people with learning difficulties reported being bullied at school.</p><p>The Government is clear that bullying, for whatever reason, is totally unacceptable. All schools are required, by law, to have a behaviour policy with measures to address all forms of bullying including that which occurs online. Schools have the freedom to shape these measures in the context of their particular local circumstances and pupils' needs. Schools are held closely to account by Ofsted for how well they deal with pupil behaviour and safety, which includes bullying.</p><p>We are also providing £4 million of funding over two years from spring 2013 to four organisations - Beatbullying, the Diana Award, Kidscape and The Anti-bullying Alliance (ABA) with the National Children's Bureau (NCB) - to develop effective initiatives that prevent and tackle all forms of bullying.</p><p>As part of their funding, the ABA has recently published a guide to cyberbullying for SEND young people, which contains advice for schools on developing effective anti-bullying practice and we link to this report in our Departmental advice on bullying.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44698/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44698/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44698/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many people with learning disabilities reported being bullied at school in each year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","193311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44700","Department for Education","false","2014-03-31","<p>The information requested is not held by the Department.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44700/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44700/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44700/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children are home-schooled in (a) Lancashire and (b) Rossendale and Darwen constituency.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","193308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44701","Department for Education","false","2014-03-27","<p>The Department for Education has reviewed evidence on the effects of one-to-one tablet schemes on pedagogy, and more broadly within education, from the UK and Australia. Positive effects on pedagogy cited within the studies considered include: improvemements to lessons and homework, characterised by more creative and engaging tasks; more and better quality feedback to pupils; and improvements in monitoring and assessment.</p><p>The Department will continue to review international research in this area, such as that being undertaken by the Creative Classroom project of the European Schoolnet organisation. This study is looking at the effects of one-to-one tablet use, in 45 secondary schools, and across eight European countries.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44701/answer",,,,,"193447","2014-03-27T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44701/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44701/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what comparison he has made with other OECD countries of the effects on pedagogy of giving one to one tablets to every pupil in secondary schools.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","193448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44702","Department for Education","false","2014-03-27","<p>The Department for Education has reviewed evidence on the effects of one-to-one tablet schemes on pedagogy, and more broadly within education, from the UK and Australia. Positive effects on pedagogy cited within the studies considered include: improvemements to lessons and homework, characterised by more creative and engaging tasks; more and better quality feedback to pupils; and improvements in monitoring and assessment.</p><p>The Department will continue to review international research in this area, such as that being undertaken by the Creative Classroom project of the European Schoolnet organisation. This study is looking at the effects of one-to-one tablet use, in 45 secondary schools, and across eight European countries.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44702/answer",,,,,"193448","2014-03-27T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44702/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44702/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment he has made of the effects on pedagogy of giving pupils in secondary schools one to one tablet computers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","193447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44703","Department for Education","false","2014-03-27","<p>The Department for Education does not procure and install broadband on behalf of schools. Headteachers manage their own budgets and are best placed to decide on their broadband requirements.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44703/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-27T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44703/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44703/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what progress his Department has made on the rollout of broadband for schools; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","193446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44704","Department for Education","false","2014-03-27","<p>The Department for Education has no baseline requirements for Wi-Fi provision in all schools. Headteachers manage their own budgets and are best placed to decide the extent of Wi-Fi provision. Where schools are built or rebuilt via the Department's capital programmes, IT infrastructure including Wi-Fi is installed to a standard that supports 1:1 tablet use in the classroom.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44704/answer",,,,,"193445","2014-03-27T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44704/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44704/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the baseline requirements are for wi-fi provision for all secondary schools to enable the use of one-to-one tablet computers in the classroom; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","193444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44705","Department for Education","false","2014-03-27","<p>The Department for Education has no baseline requirements for Wi-Fi provision in all schools. Headteachers manage their own budgets and are best placed to decide the extent of Wi-Fi provision. Where schools are built or rebuilt via the Department's capital programmes, IT infrastructure including Wi-Fi is installed to a standard that supports 1:1 tablet use in the classroom.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44705/answer",,,,,"193444","2014-03-27T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44705/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44705/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the baseline requirement is for wi-fi provision for all primary schools; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","193445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44706","Department for Education","false","2014-03-31","<p>The Department for Education publishes a list of every application received in all the completed application rounds on the gov.uk website.</p><p>Applications received in Wave 4 can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/free-schools-wave-4-application-information" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/free-schools-wave-4-application-information</a></p><p>Applications received in Wave 5 can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/free-schools-wave-5-application-information" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/free-schools-wave-5-application-information</a></p><p>Applications received in 2013 to establish free schools were part of Waves 4 and 5. As the published list states, two applications were received from groups in Lancashire in Wave 4: Burnley High School and Steiner Academy Lancaster. No applications from groups in Lancashire were received in Wave 5.</p><p>Applications received so far in 2014 are part of Wave 6. The Department for Education will publish a list of all applications received shortly after the assessment process is complete, in the same way it has for previous rounds.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44706/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44706/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44706/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what applications he received from groups in Lancashire to establish a new free school in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","193300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44707","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-03-31","<p>Estimates for the number of households which do not have mains gas and which use domestic heating oil are not available. However, the number of households that did not have access to a mains gas supply in the Rossendale and Darwen constituency can be estimated by combining figures for the lower layer super output areas that most closely match this area.</p><p> </p><p>In 2012, there were approximately 1,100 households (three per cent) which had no access to mains gas. The number of households that did not have access to mains gas in the North West is estimated to be 156,000 (five per cent of households within the North West).</p><p> </p><p>These data are available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/lsoa-estimates-of-households-not-connected-to-the-gas-network" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/lsoa-estimates-of-households-not-connected-to-the-gas-network</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44707/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44707/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44707/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate he has made of the number of properties in (a) Rossendale and Darwen constituency and (b) the North West which do not have mains gas access and which use domestic heating oil.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","193301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44708","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-03-31","<p>Electricity generation in the U.K. is privatised and the decisions on spare step-up transformers are for the individual generator businesses. Electricity transmission operations in the U.K. are private, regulated businesses. Decisions on spare transmission connected transformers are matters for the transmission businesses, to meet the licence conditions under which they operate; they form an important component in the provision of reliability of supply. The Department of Energy and Climate Change does not hold data on generator step-up transformer or transmission connected transformer quantities held as spares by industry.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44708/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44708/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44708/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many spare (a) generator step-up transformers and (b) transmission transformers are held in the UK.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","193422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44709","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-03-31","<p>The Department of Energy and Climate Change does not hold comprehensive data on generator step-up and transmission connected transformer manufacturers in the U.K. The transformers used in the privatised electricity industry are sourced from manufacturers such as Alstom Grid based in Staffordshire, among others in the UK and globally.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44709/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44709/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44709/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, which companies manufacture (a) generator step-up transformers and (b) transmission transformers in the UK.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","193423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44710","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-03-31","<p>The amounts of coal and oil imported from Russia by the UK for each year between 2008 and 2012 compared to total UK demand for those fuels are shown in the following tables.</p><p> </p><p><strong><em>Coal </em></strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><em>(thousand tonnes)</em></p></td><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Import</p></td><td><p>21,249</p></td><td><p>17,726</p></td><td><p>8,322</p></td><td><p>12,126</p></td><td><p>16,933</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Proportion of demand</p></td><td><p>33%</p></td><td><p>34%</p></td><td><p>15%</p></td><td><p>22%</p></td><td><p>25%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong><em>Primary Oil </em></strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><em>(thousand tonnes)</em></p></td><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Import</p></td><td><p>8,295</p></td><td><p>5,065</p></td><td><p>5,000</p></td><td><p>6,058</p></td><td><p>7,491</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Proportion of demand</p></td><td><p>10%</p></td><td><p>7%</p></td><td><p>7%</p></td><td><p>8%</p></td><td><p>11%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong><em>Petroleum Products </em></strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><em>(thousand tonnes)</em></p></td><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Import</p></td><td><p>1,435</p></td><td><p>2,066</p></td><td><p>2,306</p></td><td><p>2,407</p></td><td><p>2,630</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Proportion of demand</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td><td><p>3%</p></td><td><p>3%</p></td><td><p>4%</p></td><td><p>4%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>There was no gas imported directly from Russia by the UK.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44710/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44710/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44710/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what proportion of the UK's (a) coal, (b) gas and (c) oil requirements were met by imports from Russia in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","193421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44711","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-03-27","<p>Eligibility for the Enterprise Investment Scheme is a matter for HM Treasury who will be consulting stakeholders on the proposals in due course.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44711/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-27T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44711/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44711/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment he has made of the effects on the community energy sector of removing eligibility for Enterprise Investment Scheme awards from business qualifying for renewable obligation certificates.","false","Biography information for John Woodcock","Barrow and Furness","John Woodcock","193453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44712","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-03-31","<p>The value of UK imports of coal, primary oil and petroleum products from Russia between 2008 and 2012 are shown in the following table:</p><p><em>£ Million</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong><em>2008</em></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>2009</em></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>2010</em></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>2011</em></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>2012</em></strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>Coal</em></p></td><td><p>1,570</p></td><td><p>1,130</p></td><td><p>533</p></td><td><p>945</p></td><td><p>1,092</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>Primary oil</em></p></td><td><p>2,184</p></td><td><p>1,156</p></td><td><p>1,278</p></td><td><p>2,316</p></td><td><p>3,321</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>Petroleum products</em></p></td><td><p>1,091</p></td><td><p>770</p></td><td><p>1,186</p></td><td><p>1,805</p></td><td><p>1,819</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>There was no gas imported directly from Russia by the UK.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44712/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44712/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44712/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what the value of UK imports of (a) coal, (b) gas and (c) oil from Russia was in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","193420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44719","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>The quantitative risk assessment carried out prior to harmonisation with the EU pet travel rules in 2012 took into account, amongst other things, a number of variables including increases in the number of pets entering the UK. The risk assessment was published in 2011 and is available here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://archive.defra.gov.uk/foodfarm/farmanimal/diseases/atoz/rabies/documents/se0535-rabies-qra.pdf" target="_blank">http://archive.defra.gov.uk/foodfarm/farmanimal/diseases/atoz/rabies/documents/se0535-rabies-qra.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44719/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44719/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44719/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether changes in the number of puppies and dogs imported from EU member states since January 2012 are consistent with AHLVA risk assessment in 2010.","false","Biography information for Huw Irranca-Davies","Ogmore","Huw Irranca-Davies","193356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44760","Cabinet Office","false","2014-03-27","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44760/answer","PQ 193340 & 193396.pdf","PQ 193340 & 193396.pdf","Ovarian Cancer - ONS Letter","Ovarian Cancer - ONS Letter","193396","2014-03-27T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44760/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44760/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many women in Warrington were (a) diagnosed with ovarian cancer and (b) had ovarian cancer listed as a cause of death in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","193340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44774","Cabinet Office","false","2014-03-27","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44774/answer","PQ 193340 & 193396.pdf","PQ 193340 & 193396.pdf","Ovarian Cancer - ONS Letter","Ovarian Cancer - ONS Letter","193340","2014-03-27T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44774/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44774/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many and what proportion of women in (a) the UK and (b) the North West were diagnosed with ovarian cancer in the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","193396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44782","Home Office","false","2014-04-01","<p> </p><p>The Home Office talks to a wide range of partners about rural crime and theft <br>of particular commodities. However, we have not recently received any formal <br>representations about sheep rustling.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44782/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44782/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44782/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent representations she has received on sheep rustling.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","Thirsk and Malton","Miss Anne McIntosh","193320"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44783","Home Office","false","2014-04-01","<p /> <p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>I refer my Hon. Friend to the response given by the Minister for Europe (Mr David Lidington) on 24 March 2014, Official Report, column 70W. In addition, JHA agreements have also been concluded with Brazil, Ukraine and Moldova during the course of this Government which build on the borders and immigration aspects of the Schengen system, in which the UK does not participate.</p><p /> <p /> <p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44783/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44783/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44783/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44783/answer/previousversion/2687","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 19 March 2014, Official Report, column 604W, on EU Justice and Home Affairs, with which countries the EU as a legal personality has concluded co-operation agreements in the field of justice and home affairs.","false","Biography information for Dominic Raab","Esher and Walton","Mr Dominic Raab","193408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44784","Home Office","false","2014-04-30","<p>The Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) advises the Government on economic issues relating to migration.<br><br>On 1 July 2013 the MAC published a &quot;Report on the economic and labour market impacts of tier 1 entrepreneur and investor migrants to the UK&quot; which it had commissioned from the Migration Observatory. The report made a number of findings, although it concluded that it was too early to make a full assessment of the economic contribution of the two routes without further research. The report is available on the gov.uk website at:<br><br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/economic-and-labour-market-impacts-tier-1-entrepreneur-and-investor-migrants" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/economic-and-labour-market-impacts-tier-1-entrepreneur-and-investor-migrants</a><br><br>More recently, on 25 February 2014 the MAC published its own report, &quot;Tier 1 (Investor) route: investment thresholds and economic benefits&quot; in response to a Government commission. The MAC concluded that the direct investment required by the route is of little or no benefit, but there is some benefit from indirect spending by investors and their families in the UK (although this is difficult to quantify). The report is available on the gov.uk website at:<br><br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-investment-limits-and-economic-benefits-of-the-tier-1-investor-route-feb-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-investment-limits-and-economic-benefits-of-the-tier-1-investor-route-feb-2014</a><br><br>The Government keeps all routes under review and is currently considering its response to the MAC's report on the Tier 1 (Investor) route.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44784/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-30T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44784/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44784/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the contribution of the (a) Tier 1 (Entrepreneur) visa route and (b) Tier 1 (Investor) visa route on economic growth.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","193286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44785","Home Office","false","2014-03-27","<p>The Home Office accounting systems does not identify separate expenditure on the Interpol's SLTD database. The information cannot be obtained without incurring disproportionate cost.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44785/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-27T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44785/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44785/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much her Department has paid for the use of Interpol's SLTD database in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","193398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44786","Home Office","false","2014-03-27","<p>The Licensing Act 2003 bans the sale of alcohol at certain motorway service areas but this ban does not extend to all of them. At motorway service areas which are not covered by the Act, the grant of premise licences for the sale of alcohol in any particular case is at present a matter for the local licensing authority.</p><p> </p><p>The Government included motorway service areas as part of the public consultation on the Alcohol Strategy in 2012/13. The Government's response to this consultation was published in July 2013 and stated that this issue would be considered further, and it is under active consideration.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44786/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-27T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44786/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44786/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking on the decision to allow the sale and consumption of alcohol in a motorway service area.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","193334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44787","Home Office","false","2014-04-10","<p>Figures for Unaccompanied Asylum Seeking Children (UASCs) placed in Local Authority care are not available from published statistics.</p><p> </p><p>In 2012 and 2013 there were 1,125 and 1,174 applications received from UASCs, excluding dependants.</p><p> </p><p>Figures on a comparable basis are not available for previous years.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office publishes statistics on asylum applications from UASCs in tables as_08 and as_08_q (Asylum data tables Volume 2) of the release <em>Immigration Statistics </em>available from: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-october-to-december-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-october-to-december-2013</a></p><p> </p><p>This release is available from the Library of the House.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44787/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44787/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44787/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44787/answer/previousversion/2684","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many unaccompanied asylum-seeking children there were in the UK in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","193337"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44788","Home Office","false","2014-04-10","<p>Figures for Unaccompanied Asylum Seeking Children (UASCs) placed in Local Authority care are not available from published statistics.</p><p> </p><p>In 2012 and 2013 there were 1,125 and 1,174 applications received from UASCs, excluding dependants.</p><p> </p><p>Figures on a comparable basis are not available for previous years.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office publishes statistics on asylum applications from UASCs in tables as_08 and as_08_q (Asylum data tables Volume 2) of the release <em>Immigration Statistics </em>available from:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-october-to-december-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-october-to-december-2013</a></p><p> </p><p>This release is available from the Library of the House.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44788/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44788/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44788/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44788/answer/previousversion/2682","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many unaccompanied asylum-seeking children were placed in local authority care in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","193336"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44789","Home Office","false","2014-04-01","<p> </p><p>Home Office Ministers have meetings with a wide variety of international <br>partners, as well as organisations and individuals in the public and private <br>sectors, as part of the process of policy development and delivery. Details of <br>these meetings are passed to the Cabinet Office on a quarterly basis and are <br>subsequently published on the Gov.uk website: <br>http://data.gov.uk/dataset/ministerial-data-home-office</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44789/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44789/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44789/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what discussions she has had with representatives of the retail sector about measures that could be taken by shops selling alcohol to reduce the incidence of binge-drinking.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","193543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44790","Home Office","false","2014-03-31","<p> </p><p>Complaints made by, or on behalf of, detainees are managed in accordance with <br>Detention Services Order 3/2011. All allegations of serious misconduct are <br>referred to the Home Office Professional Standards Unit (PSU) for <br>investigation. These include allegations made against staff who work in the <br>detention estate or who are engaged in escorting work.<br><br>Data on the number of complaints referred to the PSU is not recorded. Only data <br>of those complaints where PSU have agreed to investigate are recorded. The <br>number investigated relating to the use of control and restraint during <br>enforced removal is detailed below.<br><br>2010 – 42 <br>2011 – 30<br>2012 – 39<br>2013 – 19 <br><br>These figures are based on management information, which is subject to change, <br>and does not form part of our publicised statistics.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44790/answer",,,,,,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44790/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44790/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-03-24","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many serious misconduct complaints related to the use of control and restraint during enforced removal were referred to the Professional Standards Unit in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","193473"
